          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "If you're staying at Portbahn House or Shorefield Eco House, a significant amount of what you'll want to do is within walking distance."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "fa8e41842f",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "6ba5788efd",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Bruichladdich Distillery: 5 minutes along the coastal cycle path. The visitor centre welcomes walk-ins without a booking."
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "listItem": "bullet",
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "9524cdcf40",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "5385570e6c",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Portbahn Beach: 5 minutes via the war memorial path — three sheltered bays with rock pools."
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "listItem": "bullet",
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "151a2adc23",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "c822bb890e",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Port Charlotte: 40 minutes on foot along the coast, 5 minutes by car. The village has the Port Charlotte Hotel, a museum, and the Lochindaal Seafood Kitchen."
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "listItem": "bullet",
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
    },
    {
      "_key": "z2qU3LP_VZoN",
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "h3",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "cUgPCZscLZOz",
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "The Jura Passenger Ferry"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_key": "8c7c23bf37",
      "_type": "block",
      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "6889a9e47b",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "From Port Askaig, foot passengers and cyclists can reach Jura on the Jura Passenger Ferry — a 5-minute crossing to Feolin. No booking required for foot passengers. The crossing runs regularly throughout the day."
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [],
      "style": "normal"
